								Git Commands With their Description.
yum install git --> This command will install the git in our server/machine.
git --version   --> This command is used to check the version of git into the system.
ls -ltr         --> This command is used to list all the files with long listing(-l), time(-t) & in recursive(-r) manner. It is used to see the detailed list including date and time.
git init        --> To initialize the git into a specific directory.
ls -ltra        --> To see the all the files including the hidden.
